items.content:
@Dan_Jeffries1 I sure do remember. 
I made fun of them.
I was right.

@bradmenezes I talk to many people working at large companies who are torn between using AI to build software and the red tape and rules imposed by IT departments.

I don't blame those departments right now: you can't just open the floodgates to vibe-coded apps. It would be a disaster.

I'm glad someone is stepping up and providing a solution for this.

@theycantkn56237 What if getting an implant would guarantee you would make a million dollars every year for the rest of your life? 

It would give you much more knowledge than a Stanford education would give you. And many other super powers.

I'll get one.

@Tiny_Fish There are two things I really like about this:

1. The structured-data part where Tinyfish strips out all of the garbage from the site and returns clean, structured data. This is key for agents and increases the chances of them succeeding at whatever task they want to accomplish.

2. The anti-bot mechanisms. A ton of websites are blocking scraping and bots, so this helps a ton.

@modelsarereal Even smart people can be dumb a lot of the time. 

Bill Gates told me my ideas had no business value when I told him to buy all of Web 2.0. (True story).

He's still a billionaire. I'm just a dumb guy with a good story.

